Yes.  Its nought but creation of a new MBean going via JMX Agent.  See 
the cmdline-jmxclient code for an example: 
http://crawler.archive.org/cmdline-jmxclient/xref/org/archive/jmx/Client.html.  
See line 250 for where we create a new Heritrix instance.
&gt;
&gt; I also been testing cmdline-jmxclient, but when I execute &quot;java -jar
&gt; bin/cmdline-jmxclient-0.10.5.jar controlRole:letmein localhost:8849
&gt; org.archive.crawler:name=Heritrix&quot;, I get the following error:
&gt;
&gt; Exception in thread &quot;main&quot; java.lang.NullPointerException
&gt;         at org.archive.jmx.Client.doBeans(Client.java:332)
&gt;         at org.archive.jmx.Client.execute(Client.java:312)
&gt;         at org.archive.jmx.Client.execute(Client.java:278)
&gt;         at org.archive.jmx.Client.execute(Client.java:256)
&gt;         at org.archive.jmx.Client.main(Client.java:159)
&gt;
&gt; Should&#39;t that list available operations and attributes? what I am
&gt; doing wrong? (If I execute without the last parameter, it runs OK and
&gt; list the differents beans).

If you do:

% java -jar bin/cmdline-jmxclient-0.10.5.jar controlRole:letmein 
localhost:8849

without the &#39;org.archive.crawler:name=Heritrix&#39; MBean name, do you get a 
listing of MBeans?  If so, find the Heritrix bean in the list and use 
the full MBean name shown here rather than 
&#39;org.archive.crawler:name=Heritrix&#39; (The latter does not look like a 
legit name for a Heritrix instance).  If not, is Heritrix being started 
in a sun 1.5.x plus JVM?  This page is good for common problems working 
w/ JMX though it is talking about embedding Heritrix. See the section 
&#39;Some problems which can occur...&#39;
&gt;
&gt; And some questions about HCC: can it be used to control differents
&gt; instances of Heritrix IN THE SAME JVM on one machine? 
Haven&#39;t tested it.  I&#39;d imagine you&#39;d write an app that first brought up 
hcc and then brought up a  Heritrix &#39;container&#39; in which to 
create/destroy Heritrix instances.  &#39;container&#39; is a not very well 
developed notion in Heritrix.  You might have to allow creation of 
default Heritrix instance because a &#39;server&#39; w/o a hosted Heritrix is 
not a concept we&#39;ve done much work on.  Rather, this kind of usage 
shoudl be happening inside a real &#39;container&#39;: a tomcat, JBoss, 
Geronimo, etc..  Its here around &#39;container&#39; where there&#39;ll be issues if 
there are to be any.   The creation of the &#39;container&#39; would register 
itself w/ JNDI.  hcc would find this registration and thereafter allow 
adding/deleting of Heritrix instances.
&gt; If the answer is
&gt; yes, can HCC create or destroy those instances?, 
It can.

&gt; or that should be
&gt; done in other way?
Less headache if you have two JVMs I&#39;d say: One for hcc and one for 
heritrix.   Should we make it so hcc can run in same JVM?

Also check out the embedding page mentioned above.  Might give you some 
ideas.

